.de Op
.BR \-\\$1 @C@ ", " \-\-\\$2
..
.TH moon\-buggy 6 "Dec 22 1998" "@MBNAME@ @MBVERS@"
.SH NAME
moon-buggy \- drive some car across the moon
.SH SYNOPSIS
moon-buggy [\-hV] @C@[\-\-help] [\-\-version]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B moon\-buggy
is a simple, curses-based game, where you drive some kind of car
across the moon's surface.  Unfortunately there are dangerous craters
there.  Fortunately your car can jump!
.SH OPTIONS
The program understands the following options.
.TP
.Op h help
shows a short but helpful message.
.TP
.Op V version
prints the program's version to standard output and exits.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I "@MBSCORE@/mbscore"
the global score file
.TP
.I "$HOME/.mbscore"
the local score file.  This is used, if
.B moon\-buggy
has no write access to the global score file.
.SH AUTHOR
The program
.B moon\-buggy
was implemented by Jochen Vo\(ss.
(voss@mathematik.uni\-kl.de).
